==Reception==
The novel won the [[Bram Stoker Award]] for [[Bram Stoker Award for Best Novel|Best Novel]] in 1996.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.horror.org/stokerwinnom.htm#1996 |title=Past Stoker Nominees & Winners: 1996 Bram Stoker Award Nominees & Winners |publisher=Horror Writers Association |accessdate=October 26, 2009}}</ref>

==Film adaptation==
{{main|The Green Mile (film)}}

[[Frank Darabont]] adapted the novel into a screenplay for a [[The Green Mile (film)|feature film of the same name]]. Released in 1999, the film was directed by Darabont and starred [[Tom Hanks]] as Paul Edgecomb and [[Michael Clarke Duncan]] as John Coffey.


